For each source, Windows Terminal JSON scheme files are fetched at a pinned
upstream commit SHA, converted to OKLCH, and republished. Per-source SHAs are
recorded in `.upstream-shas.json` and the SHA used for each individual record
is embedded as the `upstreamSha` field, with `source` carrying the source id.

When two sources emit a theme with the same slug, the source listed first in
`sources.json` wins; the dropped duplicate is logged at build time.

All original authorship of individual color schemes remains with their
respective authors as attributed in the upstream repositories.
